FSAs may establish or acquire service corporations pursuant to 12 USC 1464(c)(4)(B). A service corporation may be organized as a corporation, or may be organized in any other form that provides the same protections.

A national bank may acquire a financial subsidiary or engage in certain activities through a financial subsidiary. A financial subsidiary is any company that is controlled by one or more insured depository institutions.
Pursuant to 12 CFR 160.32, FSAs are permitted to make pass-through investments directly or through an operating subsidiary in entities that engage only in activities in which an FSA may engage.
Banks may establish or acquire bank service companies. A bank service company is a corporation or LLC organized to provide services authorized by the Bank Service Company Act.
Banks may establish or acquire operating subsidiaries. Operating subsidiaries may only conduct activities that the parent bank may conduct

Agency means any office or any place of business of a foreign bank at which balances are maintained incidental to or arising out of the exercise of banking power, checks are paid, or money is lent but at which deposits may not be accepted from citizens.

National banks may make non-controlling equity investments directly or through an operating subsidiary in certain types of entities when the investment is part of, or incidental to, the business of banking.
Bank holding company means any company that has direct or indirect control of a bank, other than few exceptions
The term representative office means any office of a foreign bank which is located in any State and is not a Federal branch, Federal agency, State branch, or State agency.

An organization chartered by the Federal Reserve to engage in international banking and financial operations. Edge corporations can be broken into Domestic Branches, Banking institutions, or Investment institutions.

For a BHC to be eligible to declare itself an FHC, all of the BHC's depository institution subsidiaries must be well-capitalized and well-managed and have satisfactory or better ratings under the Community Reinvestment Act.
The term subsidiary means a corporation over 50 percent of the voting stock of which is owned by the taxpayer.
"Branch" means any office or any place of business of a foreign bank located in any State of the United States at which deposits are received;
Commercial lending offices are similar to representative offices.  They are state licensed and cannot accept deposits, but they may borrow and lend on behalf of their parent companies.
The term public includes government owned banks that perform the functions of a central bank or a bank of issue.

The term firm is a for-profit business, usually formed as a partnership, that provides professional services, such as legal or accounting services.
The term individual includes an enterprise that is owned and run by one person and in which there is no legal distinction between the owner and the business entity.
The term custodian is a financial institution that holds customers securities for safekeeping in order to minimize the risk of their theft or loss.
The term joint includes two or more individuals or account owners who equally share its concomitant rights and liabilities.
The term corporate is a legal entity that is separate and distinct from its owners.
A government controlled entity is one which is controlled and mainly financed by government units
